# Prisma and Script Safety

- Never hardcode API tokens, cookies, or personal identifiers in scripts.
- Load operational credentials from environment variables and fail fast when missing.
- Keep destructive operations protected by explicit confirmation flags.
- Avoid running external data imports automatically on every dev startup.
- Keep migration/schema updates and script behavior reflected in repository docs.
